	'post_content' => '<p>I am a very old man; how old I do not know.  Possibly I am a hundred, possibly more; but I cannot tell because I have never <a href="#">aged as other men</a>, nor do I remember any childhood.  So far as I can recollect I have always been a man, a man of about thirty.  I appear today as I did forty years and more ago, and yet I feel that I cannot go on living forever; that some day I shall die the real death from which there is no resurrection.  I do not know why I should fear death, I who have died twice and am still alive; but yet I have the same horror of it as you who have never died, and it is because of this terror of death, I believe, that I am so convinced of my mortality.</p>',
